26 Jan 2020 16:50






Ultimately, I felt let down by Cathbhadh's message at the end.  felt like a really basic, uninteresting conclusion to all the hoops this jumps through on the way to it.

Before that, though, I was disappointed that there wasn't more focus on the oghamstone. I mean, the description is really neat, I wanted to learn more about it, sure they don't understand anything about it, but then the focus shifts entirely to D. B. Cooper.

And that wouldn't have been so bad if the fact that he was D. B. Cooper really mattered. That specific hijacking event doesn't seem to have any effect on the Foundation's ongoing search for this guy; it's just what he's most well known for. And it also bothers me  that the Foundation doesn't identify him as Dan Cooper first, since that was the guy's real pseudonym. (Unless that's actually meant as a double-blind or something.)

Point is, this has a neat idea at its core, but I just didn't enjoy the way the major parts move around it.







